    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Methionyl Oligopeptide-91 Glutaminyl Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1 sh-Polypeptide-1 Hexapeptide-40) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes from Oligopeptide-91, s-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1, sh-Polypeptide-1 and Hexapeptide-40 with the initiation code for methionine and glutamine. The fusion peptide contains 486 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
